Karstadt’s Fox Says Growth Stronger Than Expected, FTD Reports

-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 
2011-02-24T20:07:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/karstadt-s-fox-says-growth-stronger-than-expected-ftd-reports.html
Karstadt’s outgoing chief Thomas Fox
said sales at the German department store are growing faster
than the company expected,  Financial Times Deutschland  reported,
citing an interview.  Karstadt is “making money,” giving it more leeway for
investments, the newspaper cited Fox as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cornelius Rahn in Frankfurt at 
 crahn2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:  Kenneth Wong  in Berlin at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  